tuto.h1:
How to split a string using a separator in JavaScript ?

you simply use the "split" function of the String object.
This function returns an array of String that you can iterate normally :

	var singleStringWithTokens = "horse,donkey,fish,cat,spider";
	var tokens = singleStringWithTokens.split(",");
	for(var i=0; i<tokens.length; i++){
		alert("I found a pet for the day ! : " + tokens[i]);
	}
